Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.11,1:18:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It corrects itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.77,1:18:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.83,1:18:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,My question has to do with, I understand that the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.13,1:18:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,is like our animal nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.46,1:18:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And my question is
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.56,1:18:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,if the ego is like the animal,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.32,1:18:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,did God create the ego?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.55,1:18:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't really ask the question.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.51,1:18:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.77,1:18:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the way you're
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.86,1:18:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,defining the ego and God in your head.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.86,1:18:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Life evolves
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.20,1:18:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.35,1:18:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it continues
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.91,1:18:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to evolve because consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.01,1:18:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to return to its source.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.08,1:18:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,One of its potentialities,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.18,1:18:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because its potentialities
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.60,1:18:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,are unlimited,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.42,1:18:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is to evolve as the animal
